            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-history"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has no prior psychiatric hospitalisations. She was assessed by her paediatrician three years ago for a period of low mood following a change of school, at which time no formal psychiatric diagnosis was made and no medication was prescribed. There is no history of mania, psychosis, or eating disorder. She has no known chronic somatic illnesses and takes no regular medications. She reports no alcohol or substance use [MEDDIALOG:F32.9:0]. Menarche occurred at age 13 and menstrual cycles are regular. She had a single course of amoxicillin for tonsillitis two years ago, which she tolerated without adverse effects. Her BMI at today's visit is below the 25th percentile for age, consistent with recent weight loss. Physical examination and vital signs are otherwise unremarkable. Thyroid function and prolactin levels have been checked to rule out organic contributors to depression [PMID:24182617]. Family psychiatric history is notable: her mother has a history of depressive episodes and her maternal grandmother was treated for recurrent depression. There are no known cardiovascular or connective tissue diseases in the family."
          }
        ]
      }
    }
